100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 23, 1926, the British Parliament faced intense debate over the proposed new budget, with opposition parties rallying against tax increases. In the United States, the ongoing negotiations in the coal industry aimed to resolve labor disputes following the nationwide strike, raising concerns over fuel shortages amid a harsh winter. Meanwhile, in Germany, political tensions escalated as the government struggled to stabilize the economy in the wake of hyperinflation.
